Package com.eclipsesource.tabris.ui

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Action
    An Action is the abstraction of a user's interaction within a Tabris UI.
    ActionListener
    An ActionListener can be used to get notified when the user executes an Action in the UI.
    ActionOperator
    The single purpose of the ActionOperator is to modify and get the state of Action objects at runtime.
    Page
    A Page object represents a single part of a Tabris UI.
    PageOperator
    The PageOperator is used to handle pages.
    TransitionListener
    A TransitionListener can be used to get notified when the user navigates from one Page to another.
    UI
    The UI is a shared object you will find all over the Tabris UI API.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractAction
    An AbstractAction is a convenience class to make the implementation of actions easier.
    AbstractPage
    An AbstractPage is a convenience class to make the implementation of pages easier.
    ActionConfiguration
    Action objects will be instantiated by the framework.
    PageConfiguration
    Page objects will be instantiated by the framework.
    PageData
    A PageData object can be used to store page specific data and pass them from one page to another.
    TabrisUI
    The TabrisUI forms the core of the Tabris UI framework.
    TabrisUIEntryPoint
    The TabrisUIEntryPoint class should be used as the EntryPoint for TabrisUI based applications.
    TabrisUIEntrypointFactory
    A TabrisUIEntryPoint does not have a no no-argument constructor.
    TransitionAdapter
    This adapter provides an empty default implementation of TransitionListener.
    UIConfiguration
    A Tabris UI consists of Page and Action objects that are loosely coupled.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    PageStyle
    A PageStyle defines the style of a Page.
    PlacementPriority
    An enum to define the placement priority of Tabris UI elements like actions.
